title: Cross sections of some reactions induced in nitrogen, phosphorus, copper, and bromine with neutrons of energy 14.8 MeV

x4freetext: Main reference
Cross sections of some reactions induced in nitrogen,
phosphorus, copper, and bromine with neutrons of
energy 14.8 MeV
SAMES J accelerator
Deuterons on tritium, E(deuteron) = 150 keV.
Activation with absolute flux determination
via the associated particle method.
ORTEC solid-state for alpha-particles for
flux measurement.
Error quoted is standard deviation in the mean.
Uncertainty of the neutron flux
Data and comment approved by the author.
From NEUDADA files.

Positrons registered by measuring coincidences
between the two annihilation quanta.

1.5 in. diam. and 1.5 in. length were used together
with 53 AVP photomultiplier tubes in another series
of measurements
